This paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) category as it deals with designing intrusion detection systems. The use of language modeling and ensemble methods also suggests that it could belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) categories. The paper also discusses the portability of the proposed model, which could indicate that it belongs to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) category. Finally, the use of LSTM (Long Short-Term Memory) networks suggests that it could belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category.
